$ SQL Server - T-SQL / statements

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables/declare[`declare`] is needed to declare → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables[variables] or
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/cursors[cursors].

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/set[`set`] to assign values to → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables[variables] or to set boolean-like session options.

Wait (sleep) for a given amount of time with → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/waitfor/delay[waitfor delay].

Report exceptions with the → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/throw[`throw`] statement.
 
